        "improve AI citation rates",
        "monitor AI visibility across platforms",
        "optimize content for AI search engines" ;
    oc:yieldsState oc:AIBotAccessVerified,
        oc:AIVisibilityAudited,
        oc:ContentExtractabilityAssessed,
        oc:OptimizationStrategyDefined .

oc:kn_005861e2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before any AI SEO optimization effort" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Content must be indexed by each platform's search backend (Google, Bing, Brave) and crawlable by AI bots (GPTBot, PerplexityBot, ClaudeBot, Google-Extended, Bingbot). Verify robots.txt allows all AI search bots." ;
    oc:hasRationale "If content is not indexed or crawlable, no amount of on-page optimization will result in AI citation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_1f299b6d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning AI citation strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Brands are 6.5x more likely to be cited via third-party sources (Wikipedia, Reddit, review sites) than their own domains. Third-party presence is not optional — it's the primary citation pathway." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI systems aggregate information from multiple sources and trust independent third-party mentions over self-published claims." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_30165111 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing content authority signals" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Fluency + Statistics = maximum citation boost (up to 115% for low-ranking sites). The Princeton GEO research ranks: cite sources (+40%), add statistics (+37%), add quotations (+30%), authoritative tone (+25%), improve clarity (+20%)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The Princeton GEO study (KDD 2024) empirically measured these effects across Perplexity.ai responses." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3f1811b1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:directiveContent "Monthly monitoring: 1. Pick top 20 queries. 2. Run each through ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google. 3. Record citation status and competitors cited. 4. Log in spreadsheet, track month-over-month changes." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_42ccf16e a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding what content to create for AI visibility" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prioritize comparison articles (~33% citation share), definitive guides (~15%), and original research (~12%) over generic blog posts. Content type selection is the highest-leverage optimization decision." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI systems prefer structured, balanced, data-rich formats that can be cleanly extracted and cited." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5016cd11 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a user asks for traditional SEO audit or organic traffic analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill assumes good traditional SEO foundations are already in place. AI SEO adds structure and authority ON TOP of traditional SEO — it does not replace it. For technical/on-page SEO audits, defer to seo-audit skill." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Traditional SEO (crawling, indexing, backlinks) is a prerequisite for AI visibility; AI SEO layers citation optimization on top." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5d72e1af a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:directiveContent """## AI Visibility Audit Results

### Platform Coverage
| Query | Google AI Overview | ChatGPT | Perplexity | Cited? | Competitors Cited? |

### Extractability Score: X/10
- [Pass/Fail] for each check

### Three Pillar Assessment
- **Structure**: [findings]
- **Authority**: [findings]
- **Presence**: [findings]

### robots.txt Status: [bots allowed/blocked]

### Prioritized Action Plan
1. [Highest impact fix]
2. [Next priority]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Authority",
        "Extractability Score",
        "Platform Coverage",
        "Presence",
        "Prioritized Action Plan",
        "Structure",
        "robots.txt Status" .

oc:kn_60534702 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Check product-marketing-context.md for existing context. 2. Run AI Visibility Audit: test 10-20 key queries across Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity. 3. Analyze citation patterns — examine competitor content structure, authority, freshness, schema, third-party presence. 4. Check content extractability (10-point checklist). 5. Verify AI bot access in robots.txt. 6. Apply three pillars: Structure (self-contained 40-60 word passages, heading-query matching), Authority (cited sources +40%, statistics +37%, expert quotes +30%), Presence (Wikipedia, Reddit, review sites, YouTube)." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_9627ae98 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing content for AI search engines" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keyword stuffing actively reduces AI visibility by 10% (Princeton GEO study, KDD 2024). Unlike traditional SEO where it's merely ineffective, keyword stuffing is counterproductive in AI search contexts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI systems evaluate content quality and coherence; stuffing disrupts both, causing AI to de-prioritize or skip the content entirely." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9c5aec78 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any content targeting AI citation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure every key claim as a self-contained passage of 40-60 words. AI systems extract passages, not pages — each block must work independently without surrounding context." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI systems select and quote individual passages; content that requires surrounding paragraphs for meaning will be skipped." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a1d4364e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "At the start of any AI SEO task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting AI SEO work, check for product-marketing-context.md (.agents/ or .claude/) and read it. Use that context to avoid re-asking for information already covered." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Product marketing context contains brand positioning, target audience, and competitive landscape data essential for AI SEO strategy." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b5f15c56 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building an AI SEO strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Apply the three pillars framework: Structure (make it extractable), Authority (make it citable), Presence (be where AI looks). These are interdependent — missing any pillar significantly reduces citation probability." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Research from Princeton GEO study shows combined fluency + statistics yields maximum boost. Structure alone without authority signals underperforms." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_de186977 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a site's AI bots are blocked in robots.txt" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If blocked in robots.txt, unblock AI search bots (GPTBot, PerplexityBot, ClaudeBot, Google-Extended, Bingbot) while optionally blocking training-only crawlers like CCBot as a middle ground." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Blocking AI bots prevents both training and citation; the middle ground allows citation while limiting training data collection." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_eab53908 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When auditing content accessibility for AI citation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Gated content is invisible to AI systems. If your most authoritative content is behind a paywall or form, it cannot be cited by any AI platform." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI crawlers cannot authenticate or bypass gates; gated content might as well not exist for AI SEO purposes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f291830b a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating AI-optimizable content blocks (definition, statistic citation, expert quote patterns)" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## What is [Term]?

[Term] is [concise 1-sentence definition]. [Expanded 1-2 sentence explanation with key characteristics]. [Brief context on why it matters].

---

[Claim]. According to [Source], [specific statistic with number and timeframe]. [Context].

"[Expert quote]," says [Name], [Title] at [Organization]. [Context].""" .

